    "author": "1347925023961583618",
    "displayName": "1347925023961583618",
    "text": "New words I learned while reading this week \ud83d\udcda\ud83e\udd2d\n\nTouchstone \u2014 a standard or reference point used for comparison.\n\nWeathered \u2014 survived, pulled through, endured\n\nPreternaturally \u2014 beyond what is normal or natural \n\nMea culpa \u2014 an acknowledgment of one\u2019s own fault or mistake.\n\nRepugnant \u2014 extremely offensive, disgusting, or unacceptable.\n\nUmbrage \u2014 offense or annoyance taken at something.\n\nGlib \u2014 fluent and persuasive, but often insincere.\n\nCavalier \u2014 showing a dismissive or careless lack of concern.\n\nReticent \u2014 reserved or reluctant to speak.\n\nAntithetical \u2014 directly opposed or completely contrary to something.\n\nCanoodling \u2014 kissing, cuddling, or behaving affectionately in a romantic way.\n\nPontificating \u2014 expressing opinions in a self-important or dogmatic way.\n\nShoo-in \u2014 someone or something almost certain to succeed or be chosen.\n\nEbullient \u2014 cheerful, energetic, and full of enthusiasm.",
    "createdAt": "Sat Jul 11 09:44:08 +0000 2026",
    "url": "https://x.com/alexanderlinda_/status/2075878798495560032"
  },
